<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="buy-v">buy <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /baɪ/    美 /baɪ/  </p>
<p>(bought, bought) </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-vt-vi">1.★ <strong>vt &amp; vi 买；购买：</strong></h4>
<p>反 sell </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When prices are low, he buys.
一降价，他就去购物。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>buy sb sth / buy sth for sb / sth</strong>:
</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>buy him a gift / buy a gift <strong>for</strong> hi<strong>buy_2</strong>
为他买礼物</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>bought</strong> the car <strong>for</strong> $2,000.
他花2000美元买了那辆车。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>（付出一定代价）获得：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He bought fame at the cost of his health and happiness.
他牺牲健康和幸福换来了名声。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>［非正式用语］相信：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He said it was a mistake, but I don’t <strong>buy it</strong>.
他说那是个失误，但我不相信。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="buy-up">buy up</h3>
<p>1.<strong>迅速地囤积；大量买下</strong>  </p>
<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>buyer /baɪər/ n [C]  </p></div>